# Testing Overview
- Three users were involved in the prototype testing for the UniWell health tracker System
- The purpose of the testing was to evluate the usability and user experience of the system with main functions such as logging in,recording health, and veiwing progress.

# Testing Process
- The users wrer asked to perform the main functions without any prior instructions.
- The following were observed were ease of navigation, ease of understanding, the interface and ease of completeing the functions.

# Results 
- All the users were able to login to the system, record their health, and veiw their progress.
- There was a little hesitation on the users side to find the activity recording section, but users adapted quickly.
- The dashboard design, icons, and progress were praised for their clarity.

# Insights and Improvements
- The system is generally intuitive and user-friendly
- Improvemnets to be made: make the activity recording section should be more visible to the users.
- The testing has confirmed that the prototype supports the projects goal.

# Conclusion
 The user testing also confirmed that the prototype meets its primary usability goals. Some minor adjustments will also further enchance 
 the overall user experience.
